  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response to drought affected Households in Bay region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this WFP project is to save lives of 34,140 destitute and poor households that lost their main source of livelihood in the Bay region. 
With this 4,000,281 USD CERF grant, WFP will provide unconditional cash-based transfers (E-vouchers) over a period of three months. 
The project covers food security sector and will last six months. It will benefit 204,840 persons including 43,785 girls, 58,645 women and 350 people with disabilities</narrative>
  </description>
